<div id="dateline">May <em>11, 2006</em></div>

<h2>NYC, Chicago Hotels</h2>

<div id="bitenav">
<a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/news/2006/05/tantek_joins.php">&laquo; previous</a> | 

<a href="/news/">AEA News Archive</a>
 | 
<a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/news/2006/05/ny_sneak_preview.php">next &raquo;</a>
</div>

<p>Coming to An Event Apart Chicago or New York? Need a room for the night? This will help.</p>

<h3>Chicago Hotels</h3>

<p>Chicago, Chicago, that toddlin&#8217; town—where the architecture soars but prices are reasonable.</p>

<p><a href="http://amalfihotelchicago.com/">Amalfi Hotel</a><br />
29 West Kinzie<br />
Chicago IL 60610<br />
(312) 395-9000</p>

<p>&#8220;Cool, quiet, stylish, mid-priced.&#8221;—Jim Coudal.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.hotel71.com/">Hotel 71</a><br />
71 East Wacker Drive<br />
Chicago, IL 60601<br />
(312) 346-7100</p>

<p>&#8220;Downtown Chicago&#8217;s finest luxury boutique hotel.&#8221; Priced a la the Amalfi Hotel. Rooms may be slightly larger.</p>

<p>There&#8217;s also the <a href="http://www.burnhamhotel.com/">Burnham</a>, the <a href="http://www.starwoodhotels.com/whotels/search/hotel_detail.html?propertyID=2005">W Lakeshore</a>, and the <a href="http://www.chicago.intercontinental.com/">InterContinental Chicago</a>. And a <a href="http://bestwestern.worldexecutive.com/directory/usa/chicago/hotels/index.html">Best Western </a> located approximately three blocks from the Gleacher Center that as of this writing offers queen-bed rooms for $154 a night.  </p>

<p><a href="http://www.hotels.com/">Hotels.com</a> or <a href="http://www.expedia.com/">Expedia.com</a> can help you find a deal.</p>

<p>To find additional hotels near the Gleacher Center, Chicago, visit <a href="http://maps.google.com/">maps.google.com</a> and type &#8220;hotels near 450 North Cityfront Plaza Drive Chicago, IL 60611&#8221; in the entry field. Because of the way Google Maps works, you cannot bookmark the resulting page.</p>

<h3>New York Hotels</h3>

<p>New York, New York, it&#8217;s a wonderful town—especially with rooms like this.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.affinia.com/NYC-Hotel/Shelburne-Murray-Hill/Overview.cfm">Shelburne Murray Hill</a><br />
303 Lexington Avenue<br />
New York, NY 10016<br />
(212) 689-5200</p>

<p>Located mere blocks from Scandinavia House, this nicely situated retreat offers rooms that are larger than normal (by Manhattan standards), many with eat-in kitchens.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.hotelrogerwilliams.com/home.php">Hotel Roger Williams</a><br />
131 Madison Avenue <br />
New York NY 10016<br />
(888) 448 7788<br />
(212) 448 7000</p>

<p>Ritzy boutique hotel with small, chic rooms and elegant lobby, located on transitional (slightly shabby but safe) block just north of Madison Square Park.</p>

<p>If you&#8217;re an active or retired member of a uniformed service, the <a href="http://www.ssmaclub.org/">Soldiers&#8217;, Sailors&#8217;, Marines&#8217; and Airmen&#8217;s Club</a> offers clean, inexpensive rooms in a beautiful building just a couple of blocks from Scandinavia House. </p>

<p><a href="http://www.hotels.com/">Hotels.com</a> or <a href="http://www.expedia.com/">Expedia.com</a> can help you find a deal.</p>

<p>To find additional hotels near Scandinavia House, NYC, visit <a href="http://maps.google.com/">maps.google.com</a> and type &#8220;hotels near 58 Park Avenue New York City, NY 10016&#8221; in the entry field. Because of the way Google Maps works, you cannot bookmark the resulting page.</p>


